<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3784.4.4>
    bibo:endPage "444" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "401" ;
    bibo:volume "3784" ;
    dc:creator "Makarkin, Vladimir N.; Archibald, S. Bruce" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "A revision of the late Eocene snakeflies (Raphidioptera) of the Florissant Formation, Colorado, with special reference to the wing venation of the Raphidiomorpha" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252219>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252221>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252220>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252228>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252237>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252222>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252225>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252230>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252241>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252235> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252219>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Wing venation of the Jurassic Mesoraphidiidae. A, Mesoraphidia inaequalis Martynov, 1925 (Late Jurassic of Karatau, Kazakhstan), forewing. B, same, hind wing. Re-drawn with slight simplification from Martynov 1925 b. Fused veins are shown by red lines. Identity of the vein stub labeled “? ” in basal-most part of forewing is unknown. Both wings are shown with apex to right. No scale provided or pterostigma shown in original figure." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252219/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252221>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Dictyoraphidia veterana (Scudder, 1890). Holotype PU 6385, EM 1.385. A, the specimen as preserved today. B, forewing. C, hind wing. FW, forewing; HW, hind wing. Scale bars = 4 mm (B, C to scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252221/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252220>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Wing venation of extant Inocelliidae (A, B) and Raphidiidae (C, D). A, Sininocellia gigantos Yang, 1985, forewing. B, Fibla hesperica Navás, 1915, hind wing. C, Phaeostigma notatum (Fabricius, 1781), forewing. D, Ohmella casta (Aspöck et Aspöck, 1968 b), hind wing. Drawn from the photograph in Liu et al. 2012 b (A), re-drawn with simplification from Aspöck et al. 1991 (B, D). Fused veins are shown by red lines. All wings are shown with apex to right and not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252220/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Archiraphidia tumulata (Scudder, 1890). Holotype MCZ 244. A, counterpart. B, part (converted to right). Scale bar = 4 mm (both to scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252237>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Florissantoraphidia mortua (Rohwer, 1909). Holotype UCM 4512 as preserved (covered by Canada balsam). Scale bar = 4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252237/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252222>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Dictyoraphidia veterana (Scudder, 1890). Wing venation of the holotype PU 6385, EM 1.385. A, forewing. B, hind wing. Scale bar = 4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252222/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252225>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Megaraphidia exhumata (Cockerell, 1909). Holotype MCZ 3640. A, part (converted to right). B, counterpart. C, forewing venation. Scale bar = 4 mm (all to scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252225/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252230>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Archiraphidia tranquilla (Scudder, 1890). Holotype MCZ 246, the specimen as preserved. Scale bar = 4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252230/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252241>
    dc:description "FIGURE 23. ‘ Fibla’ exusta (Cockerell et Custer, 1925). Holotype UCM 4923. A, specimen as preserved. B, hind wing venation. Scale bar = 4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252241/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.252235>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Archiraphidia? somnolenta (Scudder, 1890). Holotype MCZ 488. A, part (converted to right). B, counterpart. Scale bar = 4 mm (both to scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/252235/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

